124
0:05:11.26,000 --> 0:05:13,000
Nearly all of these proteins can be explained

125
0:05:13.26,000 --> 0:05:16,000
by a single gene family,

126
0:05:16.26,000 --> 0:05:18,000
so this means that the diversity of silk types

127
0:05:18.26,000 --> 0:05:23,000
we see today is encoded by one gene family,

128
0:05:23.26,000 --> 0:05:26,000
so presumably the original spider ancestor

129
0:05:26.26,000 --> 0:05:28,000
made one kind of silk,

130
0:05:28.26,000 --> 0:05:31,000
and over the last 380 million years,

131
0:05:31.26,000 --> 0:05:34,000
that one silk gene has duplicated

132
0:05:34.26,000 --> 0:05:37,000
and then diverged, specialized,

133
0:05:37.26,000 --> 0:05:4,000
over and over and over again, to get

134
0:05:40.26,000 --> 0:05:42,000
the large variety of flavors of spider silks

135
0:05:42.26,000 --> 0:05:45,000
that we have today.

136
0:05:45.26,000 --> 0:05:47,000
